<subSubSection id="88206C549037AF0F1843EDE6F24245F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DFA2B56D8ADEF0758DF81D3319EDCC15" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1DB69D378BA25D713F1A3C0FCB80938" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Easily distinguished from more common 
<taxonomicName id="377105B3104F36CF88B1E5703E2114BF" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. ferruginea" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="ferruginea">H. ferruginea</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="974164E0FA272CECB4DC016915158625" originalValue="FallÃ©n">Fallen</normalizedToken>
by smaller body size and short feathering of the arista (Fig. 11, see also 
<bibRefCitation id="91228DC8191862FAD825B9838FA17B1A" author="Kerppola, S." journalOrPublisher="Sahlbergia" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="2 - 4" title="Hammerschmidtiaingrica Stackelberg, 1952 - Inkerinmahlanen Suomesta (Diptera, Syrphidae)" volume="17" year="2011">Kerppola (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 2-4).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DB4EE9AEAA0AA516610087CB4A9CE35E" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F6182E0F8B60ADB53B6AC43B9BA55645" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="353728C603C2CD664477C2DB5A893D1E" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Palaearctic. Few specimens are known from Finland and Leningrad province of Russia (
<bibRefCitation id="D312BCD1AD3B4CA2055C31F877DADB64" author="Kerppola, S." journalOrPublisher="Sahlbergia" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="2 - 4" title="Hammerschmidtiaingrica Stackelberg, 1952 - Inkerinmahlanen Suomesta (Diptera, Syrphidae)" volume="17" year="2011">Kerppola 2011</bibRefCitation>
). In East Russia, recorded from the republic of Tyva to Primorje region (
<bibRefCitation id="F4764DFA1128AA7B0E6A3729DAC7BA65" author="Krivosheina, M. G." journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="361 - 367" title="A review of flower-flies of the genus Hammerschmidtia of Russia, with description of larva of H. ingrica (Diptera, Syrphidae)" volume="83" year="2003">Krivosheina 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3A18A06E5B321A7B465B0AC0A4898694" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="FCED114A106C76B0EAF896B26661339C" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="925B4D1EF7791AFA400EDDF217307C19" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Saproxylic species, associated with deciduous trees (
<bibRefCitation id="3534E9619EC95E7F29B83142D5971215" author="Krivosheina, M. G." journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="361 - 367" title="A review of flower-flies of the genus Hammerschmidtia of Russia, with description of larva of H. ingrica (Diptera, Syrphidae)" volume="83" year="2003">Krivosheina 2003</bibRefCitation>
). This fly was collected from a wind-broken aspen, colonised by 7 species of macrofungi Table 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="708F85D92DEEA05E2EFE7671C3BB1528" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="29715AFC6EFE1C90A1CC071A8992A35B" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Conservation</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A4475A3E3D11FDFAE932EBC94AC399B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
